# Workspace agent instructions

Copy to `Agent.md` (or `AGENTS.md`) in your project root.
Loaded every task run into the system prompt (**default max 8000 chars**).

**Framework-bound (do not re-copy):** skills via `invoke_skill`, memory paths
(`.agent/memory/`), optional artifact paths (`.agent/plan.md`, `specs/`),
pointerize/`recall_query`, spawn_background completion notify, tool schema tips
(b64, spill). Keep this file for **project rules + work style**.

---

## Default work style (optional — project choice)

<!-- Formerly framework-built-in; pick what you want for this repo. -->

- Multi-file or >10-turn work: prefer writing `.agent/plan.md` before large edits.
- Vague/large tasks: ask 3–5 clarifying questions before destructive tools ("grill" style).
- Small 1–2 file fixes: proceed directly.
- Large HTML/JSON / quote-heavy payloads: `write_file` `content_b64` or `edit_file` `*_b64` (see tool schemas).

